            studentContoller.insertStudent(student);
        
            verify(studentService, times(1)).insertStudent(student);
        }
    
Since you controller&#39;s `insertStudent` method has no if statements and only one branch, there is basically only one test that needs to be performed, basically does the controller call the service.

Another way it can be tested is with Springs `MockMvc`.  The good thing about the `MockMvc` is that it lets you test the HTTP request.  For example in this case you would want to test that your controller&#39;s `insertStudent` method will properly respond to HTTP POST requests with a JSON Student.


